Notification _Sucked_.  If I hadn't just been looking at email, I'd of missed it.

Waiting room had no updated status.  One person dropped out.


Still, I really liked the tasks.

Time factor wise, there wasn't enough, and the logic problem was confusing; only by the last one was it clear what was going on. 

Shame, because it was sort of cool finally having some collaboration with my partner.

data.strengthInGame: The typing and word descrambling... and the logic would have been, if the timer weren't so short and it was clearer how to use the interface; that got in the way of solving the puzzle.
data.payFair: No. The pay stinks.  You should evaluate the effort here, and pay based on that. Especially if anyone on your end ever spouts off about marginalized people --- since that's who you've got on this platform. ;/  \n\nThat said, I've done far worse and demeaning actions for less. ;P
